<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css"/>
  <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
  <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/fdf00391bb.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <title>Help</title>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="main-content">
    {{>header}}

    <article class="help-info">
      <h2 class="help-info__title">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-cloud-sun" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        {{message}}
      </h2>
      
      <p class="help-info__body">
        Enter the name of a city, town, or location to check the current weather.
        The app converts the location into geographic coordinates to retrieve
        accurate weather data for that area.
      </p>
      <p class="help-info__body">
        You can choose how weather data is displayed by selecting a unit of measurement.
        Available options include Fahrenheit, Celsius, and Scientific units.
      </p>
      <p class="help-info__body">
        Weather details may include temperature, conditions, wind speed,
        humidity, and forecast information depending on availability.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="help-info" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
      <h3 id="faq-title" class="help-info__title">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-circle-question" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h3>

      <dl class="help-info__faq">

        <dt class="help-info__question">
          Why can’t my location be found?
        </dt>
        <dd class="help-info__body">
          Make sure the location name is spelled correctly or try searching for
          a nearby city. Some small or remote locations may not be available.
        </dd>

        <dt class="help-info__question">
          Why is the weather not updating?
        </dt>
        <dd class="help-info__body">
          Check your internet connection and refresh the page. Weather data
          updates depend on the availability of the external services.
        </dd>

        <dt class="help-info__question">
          What does “Scientific” units mean?
        </dt>
        <dd class="help-info__body">
          Scientific units display temperature in Kelvin and other measurements
          commonly used in scientific data.
        </dd>

        <dt class="help-info__question">
          Is my location data stored?
        </dt>
        <dd class="help-info__body">
          No. Location data is only used to retrieve weather information and
          is not stored or shared.
        </dd>

      </dl>
    </article>

    <article class="help-info">
      <h3 class="help-info__title">
        <i class="fa-solid fa-location-dot" aria-hidden="true"></i>
        Info About the APIs
      </h3>
      <p class="help-info__body">
        Weather data is provided by 
        <a href="https://weatherstack.com/" 
            target="_blank" 
            rel="noopener" 
            aria-label="Visit Weatherstack website (opens in a new tab)">
          Weatherstack
        </a>.
      </p>
      <p class="help-info__body">
        Location and geocoding data is provided by 
        <a href="https://positionstack.com/" 
            target="_blank" 
            rel="noopener"
            aria-label="Visit Positionstack website (opens in a new tab)">
          Positionstack
        </a>.
      </p>
      <p class="help-info__body">
        If a location cannot be found or data is unavailable, please double-check
        your spelling or try a nearby city.
      </p>
    </article>

  </div>

  {{>footer}}
</body>
</html>